icecast
------------------------------------------
Icecast is a streaming media server which currently supports Ogg (Vorbis and
Theora), Opus, WebM and MP3 audio streams.
It can be used to create an Internet radio station or a privately running
jukebox and many things in between. It is very versatile in that new formats
can be added relatively easily and supports open standards for commuincation
and interaction.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.4-1
  libcurl4-8.15.0-1
  libkate1-0.4.1-2
  libogg0-1.3.4-1
  libspeex1-1.2.1-1
  libssl3-3.0.17-1
  libtheora0-1.1.1-2
  libvorbis0-1.3.7-1
  libxml2-2.10.4-2
  libxslt-1.1.29-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.45-1
  cygport-0.37.2-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  libcurl-devel-8.15.0-1
  libkate-devel-0.4.1-2
  libogg-devel-1.3.4-1
  libssl-devel-3.0.17-1
  libtheora-devel-1.1.1-2
  libtool-2.5.4-1
  libvorbis-devel-1.3.7-1
  libxml2-devel-2.10.4-2
  libxslt-devel-1.1.29-1
  make-4.4.1-2
  speex-devel-1.2.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://www.icecast.org/

Canonical download:
  https://downloads.xiph.org/releases/icecast/icecast-2.4.4.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack icecast-2.4.4-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./icecast-2.4.4-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/icecast-2.4.4-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/icecast-2.4.4-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

